Notes & gotchas
	•	Thread safety: All classes above are stateless; one static ObjectMapper inside your existing loaders is fine.
	•	Null-safety: The evaluator treats missing nodes as null. becameNotNull = went from null/missing/"" to non-empty text.
	•	Dotted paths: If you’ll need nested fields later, adjust get(newDoc, "a.b.c") to split on . and walk down.
	•	Case/typing: I used .asText() for comparisons to avoid numeric vs string surprises. If you need strict numeric compare, add another op (e.g., "eqNumber").

